{"id":14881833,"mediaExerciseId":"3cf8dd57-c694-4261-bfe4-10443b51b49f","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612488,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":788,"solutions":[{"id":6018494,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"For this we will use the formula for profit which is given as:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nP&=\\text{Quantity}\\times(\\text{Expiration price - Future price})\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we have a quantity of $10$ metric tons, a future price of $\\$1974$, and an expiration price of $\\$1965$. Substituting these values to the formula, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nP&=10\\times(\\$1965-\\$1974)\\\\\n&=10\\times(-9)\\\\\n&=-\\$90.00\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThis means that their is a $\\$90.00$ loss in this futures contract. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"4f4f4217-14a0-47aa-b5ec-12b91e49712e","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":148